---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../site";
---

<BaseLayout
  path="/start-here"
  title="Start here · We Scale Startups"
  description="A guided path for post-PMF founders deciding whether WSS is for you. Three reading paths by stage, a decision tree, and a 35-minute total commitment."
  keywords="We Scale Startups onboarding, post-PMF founder guide, growth consultancy fit, which engagement first, startup growth decision tree"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Start here</p>
      <h1>Three reading paths. One 30-minute call. About 35 minutes total.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        If you're not sure whether WSS is for you — or which of the four engagements would actually help — start here.
        No demos, no sales calls until step three.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Route by commercial intent (Growth Hub: Start here as guided router) -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Which engagement?</p>
      <h2 class="route-section-h2">Pick the path that matches what you need right now.</h2>
      <p class="route-section-lede">
        Different founders arrive with different clarity. Use this to self-route — then confirm on the diagnostic.
      </p>
      <ul class="engagement-route-grid">
        <li>
          <a class="engagement-route-card" href={siteConfig.scorecardUrl}>
            <span class="engagement-route-label">I don't know what's blocking growth</span>
            <span class="engagement-route-action">Take the 5-minute scorecard →</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="engagement-route-card" href="/services/growth-diagnosis">
            <span class="engagement-route-label">I need a senior diagnosis first</span>
            <span class="engagement-route-action">Growth Diagnosis →</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="engagement-route-card" href="/services/90-day-growth-sprint">
            <span class="engagement-route-label">I need execution this quarter</span>
            <span class="engagement-route-action">90-Day Growth Sprint →</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="engagement-route-card" href="/services/acquisition-system-build">
            <span class="engagement-route-label">I need a connected acquisition system</span>
            <span class="engagement-route-action">Acquisition System Build →</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="engagement-route-card" href="/services/fractional-cmo">
            <span class="engagement-route-label">I need ongoing senior leadership</span>
            <span class="engagement-route-action">Fractional CMO →</span>
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DECISION TREE -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Decision tree</p>
      <h2>Pick the smallest commitment that answers your question right now.</h2>
      <p class="lede" style="max-width: 60ch; margin-top: 0.75rem;">
        Three honest reads — including one where we tell you not to hire us yet.
      </p>

      <div class="decision-grid">
        <article class="decision-card">
          <span class="decision-num">01</span>
          <h3>Unsure what's broken?</h3>
          <p>You suspect growth is stuck but the team can't agree what's blocking pipeline.</p>
          <p class="decision-action">Take the scorecard. 5 minutes. Score yourself across the 5 layers (positioning, acquisition, conversion, reporting, team).</p>
          <a class="button button-brand" href={siteConfig.scorecardUrl}>Take the 5-minute scorecard →</a>
        </article>

        <article class="decision-card decision-card-primary">
          <span class="decision-num">02</span>
          <h3>Know the bottleneck but need senior judgement?</h3>
          <p>You can name the constraint but want a second opinion before spending more or hiring.</p>
          <p class="decision-action">Book a 30-minute growth diagnostic. Bring the picture, leave with a plain-English read on what to do next.</p>
          <a class="button button-brand" href={siteConfig.bookingUrl}>Book a 30-minute growth diagnostic →</a>
        </article>

        <article class="decision-card">
          <span class="decision-num">03</span>
          <h3>Need proof first?</h3>
          <p>You want to see how we work before talking to us.</p>
          <p class="decision-action">Read one case study that looks like your situation. Same Problem / Action / Result format every time.</p>
          <a class="button button-brand" href="/proof">See proof →</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- READING PATHS BY STAGE -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Reading paths by stage</p>
      <h2>The honest version: WSS isn't right for everyone.</h2>

      <div class="stage-grid">
        <article class="stage-card">
          <p class="card-kicker">Pre-PMF</p>
          <h3>You're still searching for the problem.</h3>
          <p>Some signal, no repeatable customer. Growth marketing won't fix it.</p>
          <p class="stage-action">
            <strong>Don't hire us yet.</strong> Spend the time on customer research and product. Come back when there's repeatable revenue and the constraint is acquisition, not the offer.
          </p>
          <a class="card-link" href="/insights">Read why pre-PMF teams shouldn't hire a fractional CMO →</a>
        </article>

        <article class="stage-card stage-card-fit">
          <p class="card-kicker">Post-PMF, founder still selling</p>
          <h3>Paying customers, real demand, but pipeline arrives in bursts.</h3>
          <p>Founder owns every revenue call. The team is running but nobody can confidently say what's working.</p>
          <p class="stage-action">
            <strong>Best fit.</strong> Start with a 30-minute diagnostic. We'll diagnose the bottleneck and decide together whether a Sprint or Fractional CMO engagement makes sense.
          </p>
          <a class="card-link" href={siteConfig.bookingUrl}>Book a 30-minute growth diagnostic →</a>
        </article>

        <article class="stage-card">
          <p class="card-kicker">Post-PMF, scaling, plateau</p>
          <h3>£1m–£10m ARR, team in place, growth slowing or stalled.</h3>
          <p>Founder is the bottleneck on growth decisions. Channels are running but disconnected.</p>
          <p class="stage-action">
            <strong>Core fit.</strong> Read the Fractional CMO scope, then book the diagnostic. Most teams in this band start with the system build and add fractional leadership.
          </p>
          <a class="card-link" href="/services/fractional-cmo">See Fractional CMO scope →</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3-STEP PATH (kept from old version, refined) -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">If you want the short version</p>
      <h2>Three steps. No demos.</h2>

      <article class="start-step">
        <span class="start-step-num">01</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Score yourself in 5 minutes</h3>
          <p>The Growth Bottleneck Scorecard tells you which of five constraints is actually blocking pipeline. No email gating until the end.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="button button-brand" href={siteConfig.scorecardUrl}>Take the scorecard</a>
      </article>

      <article class="start-step">
        <span class="start-step-num">02</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Read one case study</h3>
          <p>Find the case that looks most like your situation. Same Problem / Action / Result format every time, readable in 60 seconds.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="button button-brand" href="/proof">See proof</a>
      </article>

      <article class="start-step">
        <span class="start-step-num">03</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Book a 30-minute call</h3>
          <p>Bring the scorecard result and your current growth picture. You'll leave with a plain-English view of the bottleneck and which engagement (if any) actually fits.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="button button-brand" href={siteConfig.bookingUrl} title={siteConfig.bookingCallReassurance}>
          {siteConfig.bookingLabel}
        </a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="shell cta-inner">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Already done step one?</p>
        <h2>Skip ahead and book the call.</h2>
        <p>Bring your scorecard result. We'll spend the 30 minutes on the bottleneck, not on intros.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button button-brand button-with-subcopy" href={siteConfig.bookingUrl} data-cta="start-here-final">
          <span class="button-label">Book a 30-minute growth diagnostic</span>
          <span class="button-subcopy">Free · 30 minutes · No pitch</span>
        </a>
        <a class="button button-light" href={siteConfig.scorecardUrl} data-cta="start-here-final-scorecard">
          Or, take the 5-minute scorecard →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="last-updated-band" aria-label="Page freshness">
    <div class="shell">
      <p>Last updated: {siteConfig.lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .route-section-h2 {
    font-family: "Fraunces Variable", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.85rem, 3vw, 2.35rem);
    font-weight: 380;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .route-section-lede {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .engagement-route-grid {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .engagement-route-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
  @media (min-width: 1100px) {
    .engagement-route-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    }
  }
  .engagement-route-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    height: 100%;
    padding: 1rem 1.05rem;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 0.85rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, box-shadow 0.15s ease;
  }
  .engagement-route-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(16, 13, 24, 0.06);
  }
  .engagement-route-label {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .engagement-route-action {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .decision-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 880px) {
    .decision-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
  }
  .decision-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.4rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .decision-card-primary {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    box-shadow: 0 14px 32px -18px color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 40%, transparent);
  }
  .decision-num {
    font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }
  .decision-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .decision-card p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .decision-action {
    color: var(--ink) !important;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding-top: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: 0.4rem !important;
  }
  .decision-card .button {
    margin-top: auto;
    align-self: start;
  }

  .stage-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 720px) { .stage-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
  @media (min-width: 1080px) { .stage-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } }

  .stage-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.4rem 1.4rem;
  }
  .stage-card-fit { border-color: var(--accent); }
  .stage-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.35;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .stage-card p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .stage-action {
    background: var(--surface-dim);
    border-radius: 0.6rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.85rem;
    margin-top: 0.85rem !important;
    color: var(--ink) !important;
  }
  .stage-action strong { color: var(--accent); }
</style>
